        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 3:01PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Limon, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Limon, Hugo, Arriba, Genoa and Cedar Point.
</description>
